9 SECTION 3. NEW AND VACANT FTE POOL - LIMITATION - TRANSFER REQUEST. The
10 governor's office may not spend funds appropriated in the new and vacant FTE pool line item in
11 section 1 of this Act, but may request the office of management and budget to transfer funds
12 from the new and vacant FTE pool line item to the salaries and wages line item in accordance
13 with the guidelines and reporting provisions included in House Bill No. 1015, as approved by the
14 sixty-ninth legislative assembly.
15 SECTION 4. ADDITIONAL INCOME - APPROPRIATION - GOVERNOR'S OFFICE -
16 BUDGET SECTION REPORT. Subject to the limitations of this section, in addition to the
17 amounts appropriated in section 1 of this Act, there is appropriated to the governor's office, any
18 additional income from other funds, excluding federal funds, which may become available to the
19 governor's office, for the period beginning July 1, 2025, and ending June 30, 2027. Any other
20 funds received under this section must be used for the specific purpose intended for the funds
21 or transferred to the appropriate state agency or institution. Upon the receipt of other funds
22 under this section, the governor's office shall provide a report to the budget section regarding
23 the source, amount, and purpose of the funds received. Federal funds which may become
24 available to the governor's office may be accepted by the governor's office. Federal funds
25 accepted by the governor's office may not be spent until authorization is received from the
26 legislative assembly or from the emergency commission and budget section under chapter
27 54-16.
